table_cells.text: Why are there so many vacant houses in my neighborhood? Can the county do something about all the boarded-up properties in District 4?
Why does District 4 have no grocery store? We have to drive across town to get basic stuff.
The sidewalks in my area are broken and dangerous—especially for seniors.
Latino businesses bring in the majority of revenue in my district. There needs to be bilingual signage for cars or pedestrians.
Not enough medical specialist, I have to drive 40 minutes to mercy hospital.
The senior center is in need of repair, can we reconcider in place of a pickleball court?
Can the county help small business owners with startup funding or low-rent storefronts?
Need better lighting and crosswalks near the school in District 2.
That dilapitaed old warehouse site in district 2 needs demolishing.
How is the county making sure new developments include affordable housing
I’ve noticed new shops opening in District 2. Will there be additional openings in district 1?
We need more affordable housing options. My kids can’t afford to live here anymore.
Thank you for the home improvement grants, our HOA has seen a lot of improvements.
The Fall Fair has been cancelled.
I want to open a restaurant that is tailored toward north african cuisine, are there any incentives for cultural business developments?
Why do national chains keep getting incentives, but we don't support local entrepreneurs?
Not enough support for small businesses
Need more kids events in summer.
Fall fair has been cancelled, replacement ideas needed.
When is the county going to clean up the lots near 8th Street? It’s an eyesore and attracts crime.
Is there any support for Black entrepreneurs trying to open businesses in District 3?”
